insights: Your enthusiasm for biology and chemistry is inspiring! Keep diving deep into these subjects, and maybe explore related online courses or workshops to further enhance your knowledge and application skills.

Joining the public speaking club is a great move! To build on your leadership skills, consider volunteering for leadership roles within the club or organizing a small event related to health and pharmacy to blend your interests.

Your interest in group work and leadership is commendable. Try to seek out group projects in your classes or initiate study groups with peers to strengthen your teamwork and communication skills in a learning environment.

Remember, being nervous about leading events is perfectly normal. Practice is key—perhaps start with smaller, more informal gatherings to build your confidence. Sharing your passion for pharmacy in these settings can also be very rewarding and informative for others.
